This article discusses the ongoing "Recovery Summer" events held by the Obama Administration to highlight the progress made by the Recovery Act in creating jobs and stimulating economic growth. Various government officials are visiting project sites across the country that have been funded by the Recovery Act. Some of the highlights mentioned include the visit of HHS Secretary Kathleen Sebelius to New Mexico to meet with tribal leaders and the groundbreaking for the Doyle Drive Replacement project in San Francisco. President Obama also spoke at the groundbreaking ceremony for a battery plant in Michigan, which is expected to create hundreds of construction and manufacturing jobs. Vice President Biden unveiled a report on the economic impact of the Recovery Act, stating that it has raised employment by between 2.5 million and 3.6 million jobs. SBA Administrator Karen Mills also visited a restaurant in Philadelphia that received a loan through the Recovery Act, highlighting the support provided to small businesses.